VOC, 10-1 overlap setting (see overleaf for results)
Within each column, find the relative gain/drop between the cells that share the color, using the formula \delta (in %) = (Rasp_IoU - WILSON_IoU) / WILSON_IoU * 100.
If the gain is positive then plot the bar with a green horizontal bar that goes from middle towards right. Otherwise, plot with a red horizontal bar that goes from middle towards left.
Then these bars should be sorted, with the highest gain-er class at the top and highest loser class at the bottom. It should be clear from the Fig 4 in the CLIP paper
